{
  "texts": [
    "In practice, the state s t includes the ego vehicle's IMU status and surrounding road entities' past poses and motion intents.",
    "These are often only partially observable.",
    "The action a t represents a sequence of future waypoints, which is translated into low-level throttle and steering control sequences via an LQR controller [20], following prior benchmarks [21, 22, 5, 13].",
    "The observation o t is captured by real sensors or rendered by a simulation engine during closed-loop evaluation.",
    "Notably, current open-loop E2E agents are trained using expert trajectories from a behavior policy π ref, inducing a state distribution d ref (s t) and yielding a supervised model πref."
  ]
}